<h2 class="govuk-heading-l" id="demand">Demand triage</h2>

<section class="developers-data-flow" id="flow-demand">
    <header class="developers-data-flow__header">
        <h3 class="developers-data-flow__title">Demand triage: submit &amp; score</h3>
        <span class="developers-data-flow__kind">Workflow</span>
    </header>
    <partial name="_DataFlowDiagram" model='("demand", flowDemand)' />
    <div class="developers-data-flow__stages">
        <h4 class="developers-data-flow__label">Captured at</h4>
        <div class="developers-data-flow__body">
            <ul>
                <li><code>POST /modern/demand</code> (initial submission).</li>
                <li><code>POST /modern/demand/{id}/exploratory</code> (analyst review notes).</li>
                <li><code>POST /modern/demand/{id}/scorecard</code> (per-question answers).</li>
                <li><code>POST /modern/demand/{id}/outcome</code> (approve / reject / defer).</li>
            </ul>
        </div>

        <h4 class="developers-data-flow__label">Stored in</h4>
        <div class="developers-data-flow__body">
            <ul>
                <li><code>DemandTriageRequest</code> for the headline.</li>
                <li><code>DemandExploratoryReview</code> for analyst notes.</li>
                <li><code>DemandScorecard</code> + <code>DemandAnswer</code> (one row per question, score + free text).</li>
                <li><code>DemandTriageOutcome</code> with <code>OutcomeStage</code>, decision date, decision-maker.</li>
                <li><code>DemandTriageAuditEvent</code> (one per state change &mdash; this is the request's timeline).</li>
            </ul>
        </div>

        <h4 class="developers-data-flow__label">Side effects on approval</h4>
        <div class="developers-data-flow__body">
            <ul>
                <li>A <code>BusinessCase</code> can be created and linked via <code>BusinessCaseProject</code> / <code>BusinessCaseProduct</code>.</li>
                <li>A <code>DemandPipelineRequest</code> is created and steps through <code>DemandPipelineStage</code> rows.</li>
                <li>On final acceptance, a <code>Project</code> (work item) is provisioned and the demand request gets the new <code>ProjectId</code>.</li>
            </ul>
        </div>

        <h4 class="developers-data-flow__label">Surfaces in</h4>
        <div class="developers-data-flow__body">
            <ul>
                <li>Demand register &mdash; <code>/modern/demand</code>.</li>
                <li>Request detail &mdash; <code>/modern/demand/{id}</code> (shows full audit timeline).</li>
                <li>Pipeline board &mdash; <code>/modern/demand/pipeline</code>.</li>
                <li>Triage-meeting agenda &mdash; <code>/modern/demand/pipeline/triage-meetings</code>.</li>
                <li>Once provisioned, the resulting work item carries <code>DemandRequestId</code> + <code>BusinessCaseId</code> on the Modern <code>WorkItem</code>.</li>
            </ul>
        </div>

        <h4 class="developers-data-flow__label">Triggers</h4>
        <div class="developers-data-flow__body">
            Notification rule emails the submitter on each <code>Status</code> change; the triage board chair is emailed when a scorecard is fully answered.
        </div>

        <h4 class="developers-data-flow__label">Downstream</h4>
        <div class="developers-data-flow__body">
            <ul>
                <li>JSON API &mdash; <code>/api/v1/demand</code> (requests, scorecards, outcomes).</li>
                <li>PowerBI &mdash; treat <code>DemandAnswer</code> as the fact (one row per (request, question)), <code>DemandTriageRequest</code> as the parent dim.</li>
            </ul>
        </div>
    </div>
</section>

