<h2 class="govuk-heading-l" id="performance">Performance reporting</h2>

<section class="developers-data-flow" id="flow-performance">
    <header class="developers-data-flow__header">
        <h3 class="developers-data-flow__title">Product return: a metric value</h3>
        <span class="developers-data-flow__kind">Timeseries</span>
    </header>
    <partial name="_DataFlowDiagram" model='("performance", flowPerformance)' />
    <div class="developers-data-flow__stages">
        <h4 class="developers-data-flow__label">Captured at</h4>
        <div class="developers-data-flow__body">
            <ul>
                <li><code>POST /modern/performance/{productDocumentId}/return/{period}</code> (Save draft / Submit).</li>
                <li>Admins reopen a closed period at <code>POST /modern/admin/performance-reporting/{productDocumentId}/reopen</code>.</li>
            </ul>
        </div>

        <h4 class="developers-data-flow__label">Stored in</h4>
        <div class="developers-data-flow__body">
            <ul>
                <li><code>ProductReturn</code> &mdash; one per <code>(ProductDocumentId, ReturnPeriod)</code>; carries <code>SubmittedAt</code>, <code>SubmittedBy</code>.</li>
                <li><code>ProductMetricValue</code> &mdash; one per <code>(ProductReturnId, MetricId)</code>.</li>
                <li>Commissions (one-off captures) use <code>Commission</code> / <code>CommissionSubmission</code> / <code>CommissionMetricValue</code> instead.</li>
            </ul>
        </div>

        <h4 class="developers-data-flow__label">Side effects</h4>
        <div class="developers-data-flow__body">
            Per-product / per-period overrides in <code>PerformanceReportingDueDateOverride</code>, <code>PerformanceReportingProductExclusion</code>, <code>PerformanceReportingPeriodExclusion</code> control whether a return is expected; submission removes the product from the &ldquo;outstanding&rdquo; list.
        </div>

        <h4 class="developers-data-flow__label">Surfaces in</h4>
        <div class="developers-data-flow__body">
            <ul>
                <li>Per-product timeline &mdash; <code>/modern/performance/{productDocumentId}</code>.</li>
                <li>Cross-product dashboard &mdash; <code>/modern/performance</code>.</li>
                <li>Reporting hub &mdash; <code>/modern/reporting/performance</code>.</li>
                <li>Operations dashboard &mdash; submission completeness tile.</li>
            </ul>
        </div>

        <h4 class="developers-data-flow__label">Downstream</h4>
        <div class="developers-data-flow__body">
            <ul>
                <li>JSON API &mdash; <code>/api/v1/performance-metrics</code> (catalogue) and <code>/api/v1/performance-metrics/returns</code> (values).</li>
                <li>PowerBI &mdash; <code>FactPerformanceMetric</code> grain is <code>(ProductDocumentId, ReturnPeriod, MetricId)</code>.</li>
            </ul>
        </div>
    </div>
</section>

<section class="developers-data-flow" id="flow-performance-commission">
    <header class="developers-data-flow__header">
        <h3 class="developers-data-flow__title">Performance commission: ad-hoc data collection</h3>
        <span class="developers-data-flow__kind">One-off campaign</span>
    </header>
    <partial name="_DataFlowDiagram" model='("performance-commission", flowCommission)' />
    <div class="developers-data-flow__stages">
        <h4 class="developers-data-flow__label">Captured at</h4>
        <div class="developers-data-flow__body">
            <ul>
                <li>Admin defines a commission &mdash; <code>POST /modern/admin/performance-reporting/commission/create</code> (name, open / close window, which metrics participate).</li>
                <li>Service owner enters values &mdash; <code>POST /modern/performance/commission/metric-value</code> (incremental save, one metric value at a time).</li>
                <li>Service owner submits &mdash; <code>POST /modern/performance/commission/{commissionId}/submit/confirm</code> seals the submission.</li>
                <li>Admin reopens &mdash; <code>POST /modern/performance/commission/unsubmit</code> clears <code>SubmittedAt</code>.</li>
                <li>Comments &mdash; <code>POST /modern/performance/commission/comments</code>.</li>
                <li>Verification / bulk approve &mdash; <code>POST /modern/performance/commission/{id}/bulk/verify</code> and <code>.../bulk/apply</code>.</li>
            </ul>
        </div>

        <h4 class="developers-data-flow__label">Stored in</h4>
        <div class="developers-data-flow__body">
            <ul>
                <li><code>Commission</code> &mdash; the commission definition; FK joins to <code>PerformanceMetric</code> select which metrics are in scope.</li>
                <li><code>CommissionSubmission</code> &mdash; one row per <code>(ProductDocumentId, CommissionId)</code>; carries <code>SubmittedAt</code>, <code>SubmittedByUserId</code>.</li>
                <li><code>CommissionMetricValue</code> &mdash; one row per <code>(CommissionSubmissionId, MetricId)</code>; carries <code>VerifiedAt</code>, <code>VerifiedByUserId</code>.</li>
                <li><code>CommissionComment</code> &mdash; threaded discussion against a submission or a value.</li>
            </ul>
        </div>

        <h4 class="developers-data-flow__label">Side effects</h4>
        <div class="developers-data-flow__body">
            <ul>
                <li>Submitting locks the submission against further save calls until an admin unsubmits.</li>
                <li>Bulk verify stamps <code>VerifiedAt</code> / <code>VerifiedByUserId</code> on every value selected; bulk apply persists any analyst decision (e.g. accept / re-baseline).</li>
                <li>Commission close (<code>CloseAt</code> in the past) prevents further submissions even if the user has not pressed Submit.</li>
            </ul>
        </div>

        <h4 class="developers-data-flow__label">Surfaces in</h4>
        <div class="developers-data-flow__body">
            <ul>
                <li>Commission dashboard &mdash; <code>/modern/performance/commission/{id}</code> (per-product progress and verification grid).</li>
                <li>Reporting hub &mdash; <code>/modern/reporting/performance</code> commission tab; <code>/modern/operations</code> commission tile.</li>
                <li>Per-product timeline &mdash; <code>/modern/performance/{productDocumentId}</code> shows commission entries alongside regular returns.</li>
            </ul>
        </div>

        <h4 class="developers-data-flow__label">Triggers</h4>
        <div class="developers-data-flow__body">
            Commission open / close windows drive the reminder schedule for participating products (via the standard performance notification rule set).
        </div>

        <h4 class="developers-data-flow__label">Downstream</h4>
        <div class="developers-data-flow__body">
            <ul>
                <li>JSON API &mdash; <code>GET /api/v1/performance-metrics/commissions</code> returns commissions, submissions and values.</li>
                <li>PowerBI &mdash; treat <code>CommissionMetricValue</code> as a fact at grain <code>(ProductDocumentId, CommissionId, MetricId)</code>; join to <code>DimProduct</code> via <code>ProductDocumentId</code> and to <code>DimMetric</code> via <code>MetricId</code>.</li>
            </ul>
        </div>
    </div>
</section>

