<h2 class="govuk-heading-l" id="standards">Standards management</h2>
<p class="developers-data-flow-group__intro">
    Standards run a staged lifecycle &mdash; <strong>Draft &rarr; Under Review &rarr;
    Approved &rarr; Published</strong> &mdash; with stage transitions kept on the
    standard itself plus a comment trail. Functional standards are assessed
    against published criteria; assessment responses are the fact data for
    PowerBI.
</p>

<section class="developers-data-flow" id="flow-standards-ddt">
    <header class="developers-data-flow__header">
        <h3 class="developers-data-flow__title">DDT standard: draft &rarr; approve &rarr; publish</h3>
        <span class="developers-data-flow__kind">Lifecycle</span>
    </header>
    <partial name="_DataFlowDiagram" model='("standards-ddt", flowStandardsDdt)' />
    <div class="developers-data-flow__stages">
        <h4 class="developers-data-flow__label">Captured at</h4>
        <div class="developers-data-flow__body">
            <ul>
                <li>Create draft &mdash; <code>POST /modern/standards/ddt/create</code> &rarr; <code>DdtCreatePost</code>. New <code>DdtStandard</code> row at <code>Stage = Draft</code>, version <code>0.1.0</code>, <code>StandardUuid</code> stable across the lifecycle.</li>
                <li>Edit existing &mdash; <code>POST /modern/standards/ddt/{id}/start-edit</code> spawns a <strong>child draft</strong> with <code>ParentStandardId</code> set, leaving the published version intact. Subsequent edits hit <code>POST /modern/standards/ddt/{id}/edit</code>.</li>
                <li>Submit for review &mdash; <code>POST /modern/standards/ddt/{id}/submit-for-review</code> moves <code>Stage</code> to <code>Under Review</code>.</li>
                <li>Approve / reject &mdash; <code>POST .../approve</code> and <code>POST .../reject</code> respectively; both write a <code>DdtStandardComment</code> with the reviewer and reason.</li>
                <li>Publish &mdash; <code>POST /modern/standards/ddt/{id}/publish</code>.</li>
                <li>Delete / unpublish &mdash; <code>POST /modern/standards/ddt/{id}/delete</code>.</li>
            </ul>
        </div>

        <h4 class="developers-data-flow__label">Stored in</h4>
        <div class="developers-data-flow__body">
            <ul>
                <li><code>DdtStandard</code> &mdash; <code>StandardUuid</code>, <code>Stage</code>, <code>IsPublished</code>, <code>PublishedAt</code>, <code>FirstPublished</code>, <code>Version</code>, <code>GovernanceApproval</code>, <code>ParentStandardId</code>.</li>
                <li>Content joins &mdash; <code>DdtStandardOwner</code>, <code>DdtStandardContact</code>, <code>DdtStandardCategory</code>, <code>DdtStandardSubCategory</code>, <code>DdtStandardPhase</code>, <code>DdtStandardValidationRule</code>, <code>DdtStandardProduct</code>, <code>DdtStandardException</code>.</li>
                <li>Audit &mdash; <code>DdtStandardComment</code> (one row per transition with author + comment), <code>DdtStandardUnpublishAudit</code>, <code>DdtStandardVersion</code> (snapshot of published content).</li>
            </ul>
        </div>

        <h4 class="developers-data-flow__label">Side effects</h4>
        <div class="developers-data-flow__body">
            <ul>
                <li><strong>Approve</strong> sets <code>GovernanceApproval = true</code> and clears any prior rejection state.</li>
                <li><strong>Publish</strong> stamps <code>PublishedAt</code>, increments <code>Version</code>, sets <code>FirstPublished</code> if not previously set, and snapshots the current content into <code>DdtStandardVersion</code>. If the row is a child draft, the parent <code>DdtStandard</code> is updated in-place and the child is consumed (parent retains <code>StandardUuid</code>).</li>
                <li>Standard <code>AuditLog</code> entry written for every stage change.</li>
            </ul>
        </div>

        <h4 class="developers-data-flow__label">Surfaces in</h4>
        <div class="developers-data-flow__body">
            <ul>
                <li>Catalogue &mdash; <code>/modern/standards/ddt</code> (filters by stage, owner, category).</li>
                <li>Detail &mdash; <code>/modern/standards/ddt/{id}</code> with tabs for purpose, criteria, how-to-meet, related guidance, approved products and exceptions.</li>
                <li>Management hub &mdash; <code>/modern/standards/management</code>; <code>POST /modern/standards/management/products/{id}/approve</code> approves the product against current published standards.</li>
                <li>Per-product compliance card &mdash; surfaced on service-register product detail.</li>
            </ul>
        </div>

        <h4 class="developers-data-flow__label">Triggers</h4>
        <div class="developers-data-flow__body">
            Stage transitions append to <code>DdtStandardComment</code> and write <code>AuditLog</code>; reviewers / publishers are notified via the standard notification ruleset when configured. Unpublishing creates a <code>DdtStandardUnpublishAudit</code> row that captures the reason.
        </div>

        <h4 class="developers-data-flow__label">Downstream</h4>
        <div class="developers-data-flow__body">
            <ul>
                <li>JSON API &mdash; <code>GET /api/DdtStandards</code>, <code>/api/DdtStandards/Exceptions</code>, <code>/api/DdtStandards/ApprovedProducts</code>.</li>
                <li>PowerBI &mdash; <code>DimStandard</code> keyed by <code>StandardUuid</code> (stable across versions); join <code>DdtStandardVersion</code> as a slowly-changing history table for trend analysis.</li>
            </ul>
        </div>
    </div>
</section>

<section class="developers-data-flow" id="flow-standards-functional">
    <header class="developers-data-flow__header">
        <h3 class="developers-data-flow__title">Functional standard: conduct an assessment</h3>
        <span class="developers-data-flow__kind">Per-criterion responses</span>
    </header>
    <partial name="_DataFlowDiagram" model='("standards-functional", flowStandardsAssessment)' />
    <div class="developers-data-flow__stages">
        <h4 class="developers-data-flow__label">Captured at</h4>
        <div class="developers-data-flow__body">
            <ul>
                <li>Conduct &mdash; <code>GET /modern/standards/functional/assessment/{id}/conduct</code> renders the response form.</li>
                <li>Save (autosave per criterion) &mdash; <code>POST /modern/standards/functional/assessment/save-response</code> writes one <code>AssessmentCriteriaResponse</code> row.</li>
                <li>Submit &mdash; <code>POST /modern/standards/functional/assessment/submit</code> stamps <code>SubmittedAt</code> on <code>FunctionalStandardAssessment</code>.</li>
                <li>Delete &mdash; <code>POST /modern/standards/functional/assessment/delete</code> soft-deletes the assessment and its responses.</li>
            </ul>
        </div>

        <h4 class="developers-data-flow__label">Stored in</h4>
        <div class="developers-data-flow__body">
            <ul>
                <li><code>FunctionalStandardAssessment</code> &mdash; one row per (standard, assessed work-item or service); carries <code>SubmittedAt</code>, <code>AssessmentLeadUserId</code>.</li>
                <li><code>AssessmentCriteriaResponse</code> &mdash; one row per <code>CriterionId</code>, with <code>Attainment</code> (a numeric level) and <code>Notes</code>.</li>
                <li>Catalogue &mdash; <code>FunctionalStandard</code>, <code>FunctionalStandardTheme</code>, <code>FunctionalStandardPracticeArea</code>, <code>AssessmentCriterion</code>.</li>
            </ul>
        </div>

        <h4 class="developers-data-flow__label">Side effects</h4>
        <div class="developers-data-flow__body">
            <ul>
                <li>Scores are derived on read: practice-area = average of criterion <code>Attainment</code>; theme = average of practice-area scores. Nothing is denormalised &mdash; the responses are the source of truth.</li>
                <li>Submission opens the Word / Excel exports (drafts are export-restricted).</li>
            </ul>
        </div>

        <h4 class="developers-data-flow__label">Surfaces in</h4>
        <div class="developers-data-flow__body">
            <ul>
                <li>Summary &mdash; <code>/modern/standards/functional/assessment/{id}/summary</code>.</li>
                <li>Catalogue &mdash; <code>/modern/standards/functional</code> shows the latest assessment status per standard / subject.</li>
                <li>Work-item / Service standards card surfaces the most recent assessment overall.</li>
            </ul>
        </div>

        <h4 class="developers-data-flow__label">Downstream</h4>
        <div class="developers-data-flow__body">
            <ul>
                <li>Word export &mdash; <code>GET /modern/standards/functional/assessment/{id}/export/word</code>.</li>
                <li>Excel export &mdash; <code>GET /modern/standards/functional/assessment/{id}/export</code>.</li>
                <li>PowerBI &mdash; <code>FactAssessmentResponse</code> grain is <code>(AssessmentId, CriterionId)</code>; join to <code>DimCriterion</code> on <code>CriterionId</code>, then up to <code>DimStandard</code> / <code>DimSubject</code> through the catalogue tables.</li>
            </ul>
        </div>
    </div>
</section>

