<h2 class="govuk-heading-l" id="cross-cutting">Cross-cutting flows</h2>

<section class="developers-data-flow" id="cross-cms-sync">
    <header class="developers-data-flow__header">
        <h3 class="developers-data-flow__title">Upstream: CMDB sync (Sync settings)</h3>
        <span class="developers-data-flow__kind">Operator-driven sync</span>
    </header>
    <p class="developers-data-flow-group__intro govuk-!-margin-bottom-3 govuk-!-padding-left-4 govuk-!-padding-right-4 govuk-!-padding-top-3">
        Service-register data is brought in from the on-prem CMDB by an
        operator on
        <code>/modern/operations/service-register/sync-settings</code>. The
        page exposes three flows: a <strong>bulk sync</strong> (Sync from CMDB
        button, with live SSE progress), a <strong>per-product sync</strong>
        from the product detail page, and a <strong>completion-template
        import</strong> for fields the CMDB does not own. All three apply
        configurable sync rules (<code>FipsCmdbSyncRule</code>) and write a
        run record to <code>FipsSyncHistory</code>.
    </p>
    <partial name="_DataFlowDiagram" model='("cmdb-sync", flowCmdbSync)' />
    <div class="developers-data-flow__stages">
        <h4 class="developers-data-flow__label">Captured at</h4>
        <div class="developers-data-flow__body">
            <ul>
                <li>Sync settings hub &mdash; <code>GET /modern/operations/service-register/sync-settings</code> (controller: <code>ServiceRegisterSyncSettings</code>). Houses all three actions below.</li>
                <li>Bulk sync &mdash; <code>POST /modern/operations/service-register/sync-cmdb-stream</code> streams Server-Sent Events while running (used by the in-page modal). The non-streaming variant is <code>POST .../sync-cmdb</code>.</li>
                <li>Per-product sync &mdash; <code>POST /modern/operations/service-register/product/{id}/sync-cmdb-json</code> from the product detail page.</li>
                <li>Completion import &mdash; <code>POST .../sync-settings/import-completion</code> (CSV template from <code>GET .../sync-settings/export-completion</code>).</li>
                <li>Sync rules CRUD &mdash; <code>.../sync-settings/add</code>, <code>.../sync-settings/{id}/toggle</code>, <code>.../sync-settings/{id}/delete</code>, <code>.../sync-settings/reset-products-for-cmdb</code>.</li>
            </ul>
        </div>

        <h4 class="developers-data-flow__label">Stored in</h4>
        <div class="developers-data-flow__body">
            <ul>
                <li><code>FipsService</code> &mdash; canonical product / service row, upserted by CMDB <code>sys_id</code>.</li>
                <li><code>CMDBProduct</code> &mdash; last-known CMDB attributes for the row.</li>
                <li><code>FipsCmdbSyncRule</code> &mdash; operator-defined rules (pattern + match kind + target status / &ldquo;enterprise service&rdquo; flag).</li>
                <li><code>FipsSyncHistory</code> &mdash; one row per bulk run with counts and error samples.</li>
                <li><code>FipsCompletionImportResult</code> &mdash; per-upload summary returned to the banner.</li>
            </ul>
        </div>

        <h4 class="developers-data-flow__label">Side effects</h4>
        <div class="developers-data-flow__body">
            <ul>
                <li>Rules are evaluated per row: matching rows can have their status set (Rejected, Inactive, etc.) or be flagged as enterprise services.</li>
                <li>Rows already retired in COMPASS are left alone; CMDB rows without a <code>sys_id</code> are skipped (counted in the result).</li>
                <li>Default rules are seeded on first run via <code>EnsureDefaultCmdbSyncRulesAsync</code>.</li>
                <li>Product categories are not synced &mdash; they are managed manually inside COMPASS.</li>
            </ul>
        </div>

        <h4 class="developers-data-flow__label">Surfaces in</h4>
        <div class="developers-data-flow__body">
            <ul>
                <li>Service register &mdash; <code>/modern/operations/service-register</code> (active tab redirected to after bulk sync).</li>
                <li>Product detail &mdash; <code>/modern/operations/service-register/product/{id}</code> (the per-product sync button lives here).</li>
                <li>Sync settings page itself &mdash; rules list, completion import results, run history.</li>
                <li>Product picker &mdash; on work-item create / edit and on RAID risk / issue / action create forms.</li>
                <li>RAID records that carry <code>ProductDocumentId</code> render the product name via this table.</li>
            </ul>
        </div>

        <h4 class="developers-data-flow__label">Triggers</h4>
        <div class="developers-data-flow__body">
            Completion import shows a notification banner with row counts; sync errors are surfaced as a TempData error with up to a handful of error samples. No outbound email.
        </div>

        <h4 class="developers-data-flow__label">Downstream</h4>
        <div class="developers-data-flow__body">
            <ul>
                <li>JSON API &mdash; <code>/api/v1/service-register</code>.</li>
                <li>PowerBI &mdash; use as <code>DimProduct</code>. Join key on every fact table is <code>ProductDocumentId</code> (string), not <code>FipsService.Id</code>.</li>
            </ul>
        </div>
    </div>
</section>

<section class="developers-data-flow" id="cross-notifications">
    <header class="developers-data-flow__header">
        <h3 class="developers-data-flow__title">Outbound: a notification email</h3>
        <span class="developers-data-flow__kind">Outbound</span>
    </header>
    <partial name="_DataFlowDiagram" model='("notifications", flowNotifications)' />
    <div class="developers-data-flow__stages">
        <h4 class="developers-data-flow__label">Captured at</h4>
        <div class="developers-data-flow__body">
            Rules are configured at <code>/modern/admin/notification-settings</code> &mdash; one <code>NotificationRule</code> per (trigger, template, recipient strategy).
        </div>

        <h4 class="developers-data-flow__label">Stored in</h4>
        <div class="developers-data-flow__body">
            <ul>
                <li><code>NotificationRule</code> &mdash; trigger + template ref + recipient strategy.</li>
                <li><code>NotificationTemplate</code> &mdash; GOV.Notify template id and placeholders.</li>
                <li><code>NotificationLog</code> &mdash; one row per send attempt (status, GOV.Notify id, error).</li>
            </ul>
        </div>

        <h4 class="developers-data-flow__label">Side effects</h4>
        <div class="developers-data-flow__body">
            Recipient resolution consults the work-item contact tables (<code>ProjectSeniorResponsibleOfficer</code>, <code>ProjectServiceOwner</code>, <code>ProjectPmoContact</code>, <code>Project.PrimaryContactUserId</code>, <code>ProjectBudgetOwner</code>) and the underlying <code>User</code> records.
        </div>

        <h4 class="developers-data-flow__label">Surfaces in</h4>
        <div class="developers-data-flow__body">
            <ul>
                <li>Notification log &mdash; <code>/modern/admin/notification-settings/log</code>.</li>
                <li>Per-user inbox (out of band).</li>
            </ul>
        </div>

        <h4 class="developers-data-flow__label">Downstream</h4>
        <div class="developers-data-flow__body">
            None internal; the log is the source of truth for "did we send this".
        </div>
    </div>
</section>

<section class="developers-data-flow" id="cross-audit">
    <header class="developers-data-flow__header">
        <h3 class="developers-data-flow__title">Cross-cutting: audit &amp; observability</h3>
        <span class="developers-data-flow__kind">Background</span>
    </header>
    <partial name="_DataFlowDiagram" model='("audit", flowAudit)' />
    <div class="developers-data-flow__stages">
        <h4 class="developers-data-flow__label">Stored in</h4>
        <div class="developers-data-flow__body">
            <ul>
                <li><code>AuditLog</code> &mdash; one row per write (entity type, id, action, user, payload JSON).</li>
                <li>Per-domain history tables &mdash; <code>ProjectRagHistory</code>, <code>IssueHistory</code>, <code>ProjectProblemStatementHistory</code>, <code>DemandTriageAuditEvent</code>, <code>BusinessCaseDdtFeedback</code>, <code>AuditHistory</code> (accessibility).</li>
                <li><code>ApiRequestLog</code> &mdash; every API call (token, method, path, status, duration).</li>
            </ul>
        </div>

        <h4 class="developers-data-flow__label">Surfaces in</h4>
        <div class="developers-data-flow__body">
            <ul>
                <li>Per-work-item audit tab &mdash; <code>/modern/work/{id}/audit</code> (renders <code>LifecycleAuditEntry</code> rows).</li>
                <li>Per-RAID-item timeline &mdash; <code>/modern/raid/review/work/item/{kind}/{id}/timeline</code>.</li>
                <li>API token usage &mdash; <code>/modern/admin/api-tokens/{id}</code>.</li>
            </ul>
        </div>
    </div>
</section>

